description:
Get details for a specific client.

## Response 200
```json
{
  "success": true,
  "client": {
    "clientId": "restaurant-001",
    "connectedAt": "...",
    "lastHeartbeat": "...",
    "status": "connected",
    "metadata": {},
    "downloadHistory": []
  }
}
```

## Response 404
```json
{
  "success": false,
  "error": { "code": "CLIENT_NOT_FOUND", "message": "..." }
}
```

## Blocked By: 5.3

Create utilities for calculating and verifying checksums.

## Files to Create
- server/src/utils/checksum.js
- client/src/utils/checksum.js (can be identical)

## API to Export
- calculateChecksum(buffer) -> string (hex SHA-256)
- calculateFileChecksum(filePath) -> Promise<string> (streams file)
- verifyChecksum(data, expectedChecksum) -> boolean

## Implementation
```javascript
const crypto = require('crypto');

function calculateChecksum(buffer) {
  return crypto.createHash('sha256').update(buffer).digest('hex');
}

async function calculateFileChecksum(filePath) {
  // Stream file through hash
}

function verifyChecksum(data, expected) {
  return calculateChecksum(data) === expected;
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- calculateChecksum returns consistent SHA-256 hex string
- calculateFileChecksum works with large files (streaming)
- verifyChecksum correctly validates data integrity

